{
  "page": "Shield of the Faith",
  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p><b>Shield of the Faith</b> is an honorary title claimed by the Lord of <a href=\"/index.php/House_Manderly\" title=\"House Manderly\">House Manderly</a> of <a href=\"/index.php/White_Harbor\" title=\"White Harbor\">White Harbor</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd19.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd19.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> It showcases House Manderly's allegiance to the <a href=\"/index.php/Faith_of_the_Seven\" title=\"Faith of the Seven\">Faith of the Seven</a>, although it is unknown whether the title is recognized by the <a href=\"/index.php/High_Septon\" title=\"High Septon\">High Septon</a> and the <a href=\"/index.php/Most_Devout\" title=\"Most Devout\">Most Devout</a>.\n</p><p>Being exiles from the <a href=\"/index.php/Reach\" title=\"Reach\">Reach</a>, the Manderlys are the most prominent of the few houses of the <a href=\"/index.php/North\" title=\"North\">north</a> who adhere to the Faith,<sup id=\"cite_ref-Ragot53.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ragot53.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> others being the more minor House <a href=\"/index.php/House_Whitehill\" title=\"House Whitehill\">Whitehill</a> and possibly House <a href=\"/index.php/House_Wells_(the_North)\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"House Wells (the North)\">Wells</a>. Most northern followers of the Faith live in the south of the region.<sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup> Known northern septs include the <a href=\"/index.php/Sept_of_the_Snows\" title=\"Sept of the Snows\">Sept of the Snows</a> at White Harbor<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd15.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd15.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup> and a small sept at <a href=\"/index.php/Winterfell\" title=\"Winterfell\">Winterfell</a> built for <a href=\"/index.php/Catelyn_Tully\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Catelyn Tully\">Catelyn Tully</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Ragot48.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_5-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ragot48.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span id=\"Known_Shield's_of_the_Faith\"></span><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Known_Shield.27s_of_the_Faith\">Known Shield's of the Faith</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Shield_of_the_Faith&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Known Shield&#039;s of the Faith\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><a href=\"/index.php/Wyman_Manderly\" title=\"Wyman Manderly\">Wyman Manderly</a>, Lord of White Harbor, is the current Shield of the Faith.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd19.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd19.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"See_also\">See also</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Shield_of_the_Faith&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: See also\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><a href=\"/index.php/Lord_Marshal_of_the_Mander\" title=\"Lord Marshal of the Mander\">Lord Marshal of the Mander</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/Defender_of_the_Dispossessed\" title=\"Defender of the Dispossessed\">Defender of the Dispossessed</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/Warden_of_the_White_Knife\" title=\"Warden of the White Knife\">Warden of the White Knife</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/Lord_of_White_Harbor\" title=\"Lord of White Harbor\">Lord of White Harbor</a></li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Shield_of_the_Faith&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: References\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"references-small\" style=\"-webkit-column-width:200px; -moz-column-width:200px; column-width:200px; -webkit-column-count:2; -moz-column-count:2; column-count:2;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-Radwd19.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Radwd19.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\">1.0</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Radwd19.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\">1.1</a></sup></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Dance_with_Dragons\" title=\"A Dance with Dragons\">A Dance with Dragons</a></i>, <a href=\"/index.php/A_Dance_with_Dragons-Chapter_19\" title=\"A Dance with Dragons-Chapter 19\">Chapter 19</a>, Davos III.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Ragot53.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-Ragot53.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Game_of_Thrones\" title=\"A Game of Thrones\">A Game of Thrones</a></i>, <a href=\"/index.php/A_Game_of_Thrones-Chapter_53\" title=\"A Game of Thrones-Chapter 53\">Chapter 53</a>, Bran VI.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-3\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a href=\"/index.php/So_Spake_Martin\" title=\"So Spake Martin\">So Spake Martin</a>: <a cla